        "help": "Why: Static id attributes can cause duplicate IDs when components are rendered multiple times, leading to accessibility issues and broken functionality (e.g., label-input associations).\nFix: Use useId() from Vue 3.5+:\n  <script setup>\n  import { useId } from 'vue'\n  \n  const id = useId()\n  </script>\n  \n  <template>\n  <label :for=\"id\">Name:</label>\n  <input :id=\"id\" type=\"text\">\n  </template>\nBenefits:\n- Generates unique IDs for each component instance\n- Stable across server and client rendering (SSR-safe)\n- Works with labels, ARIA attributes, and form associations"
      },
      {
        "ruleId": "vue/attribute-order",
        "severity": 1,
        "message": "[vize:vue/attribute-order] Attribute should be placed in correct order",
        "line": 1,
        "column": 487,
        "endLine": 1,
        "endColumn": 501,
        "help": "Reorder attributes to follow the recommended order"
      },
      {
